Which command should be used to make changes to the choices made when a Debianpackage was installed?
A)  dpkg- reconfigure
B)  dpkg - r
C)  dpkg reconf
D)  apt- get reinstall
A
A. The dpkg- reconfigure program will cause an already- installed package to be recon-figured or changed. The - r option for dpkg removes a package, thus making option Bincorrect. There is no reconf option for dpkg or reinstall option for apt- get.
